bg.x2d.geo

Class PointUD

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.geom.Point2D
      • java.awt.Point
        • bg.x2d.geo.PointUD
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable

    public class PointUD
extends Point
    Point Universal-Double. Implementation of a 2D point that stores its value as a double and allows quick access to it as long, int, and float. Qualifies polymorphically as a Point or Point2D, so it can often be passed to Java2D functions (including AWT/Swing).

    The coordinates can be accessed directly via fields ux and uy, although changes to the data should be made ideally through setLocation to ensure that the changes are also reflected in all of PointUD's inherited methods/fields.
    Since:
    2DX 1.0 (1st Edition)
    Author:
    Brian Groenke
    See Also:
